Cyclone Sidr, a powerful storm with winds up to 240 km/h, hit Bangladesh's coast near the India border.
Evacuations were underway in both countries to save lives.
The cyclone, visible from space, caused devastation in rural areas.
The United States and Germany offered aid to help victims.
Hundreds died, and thousands were left homeless.
The storm weakened as it moved inland, but the impact was severe.
Emergency relief efforts were in full swing to provide shelter, water, and medical assistance to those affected.
The international community joined hands to support Bangladesh in this time of crisis.
